==English==
===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/pɒnˈtuːn/}}
*{{SAMPA|/pQn"tu:n/}}

===Etymology 1===
From Old (and modern) French [[ponton]], from Latin [[ponto]] ‘ferryboat’, from [[pons]] ‘bridge’.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# (''Military'') A flat-bottomed boat used as a support for a temporary bridge.
# A floating structure used as a bridge or dock.
# A box used to raise a sunken vessel.
# A float of a seaplane.

=====Synonyms=====
*(''floating structure used as a bridge''): [[pontoon bridge]]

